00:25:25,790 --> 00:25:27,990
I was indeed assaulted by Yang Weida.

565
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:30,240
When Ms. Xia approached you,

566
00:25:30,270 --> 00:25:32,330
did she promise to give you a benefit?

567
00:25:34,140 --> 00:25:36,390
Ms. Shan, please be honest with us.

568
00:25:36,420 --> 00:25:37,440
Otherwise, when the case is taken to court,

569
00:25:37,440 --> 00:25:39,240
there could serious consequences.

570
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:41,710
In fact, it's not much of a benefit.

571
00:25:41,990 --> 00:25:44,230
When Ms. Xia came to my place,

572
00:25:44,420 --> 00:25:46,230
my landlord was urging me to pay the rent.

573
00:25:46,230 --> 00:25:47,630
But I couldn't afford it.

574
00:25:47,710 --> 00:25:49,870
So Ms. Xia paid two months' rent for me.

575
00:25:51,240 --> 00:25:52,300
Ms. Xia also told me

576
00:25:52,310 --> 00:25:54,030
that even after the case was over,

577
00:25:54,030 --> 00:25:56,290
I could still ask her for help at any time.

578
00:25:59,710 --> 00:26:01,370
Why do you want to take it back?

579
00:26:01,790 --> 00:26:02,710
We found that

580
00:26:02,710 --> 00:26:04,570
this piece of evidence is flawed.

581
00:26:04,690 --> 00:26:06,570
But you don't have much evidence.

582
00:26:06,790 --> 00:26:07,990
With this going away,

583
00:26:08,030 --> 00:26:10,290
it's possible that you can't make a case.

584
00:26:10,780 --> 00:26:12,690
We'll take it back for discussion.

585
00:26:12,690 --> 00:26:13,480
Then we'll make a final decision.

586
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:15,680
Thank you, Ms. Su. Thanks for your time.

587
00:26:16,330 --> 00:26:17,370
It doesn't matter

588
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:19,190
if I can't make money from this lawsuit.

589
00:26:19,190 --> 00:26:20,870
I just can't accept that because of you,

590
00:26:20,870 --> 00:26:22,470
I appeared unprofessional before the judge.

591
00:26:22,470 --> 00:26:23,410
I think this lawsuit should be dropped

592
00:26:23,410 --> 00:26:24,810
as soon as possible. Bye.

593
00:26:33,470 --> 00:26:34,140
You're back!

594
00:26:34,140 --> 00:26:35,800
Wait for me to finish the game.

595
00:26:37,270 --> 00:26:38,650
What are you doing? I was about to get on a higher level.

596
00:26:38,650 --> 00:26:40,310
Why did you bribe the witness?

597
00:26:40,630 --> 00:26:41,520
Who did I bribe?

598
00:26:41,540 --> 00:26:42,620
Shan Guiping.

599
00:26:42,650 --> 00:26:44,910
Didn't you give her money to pay her rent?

600
00:26:45,020 --> 00:26:46,560
Do you think you can conceal it?

601
00:26:46,560 --> 00:26:47,990
Now, not only do we know that,

602
00:26:47,990 --> 00:26:49,270
the defendant counsel has also found it out.

603
00:26:49,270 --> 00:26:50,910
Do you want to help the haters,

604
00:26:50,910 --> 00:26:52,550
and get us disbarred? Will that make you happy?

605
00:26:52,550 --> 00:26:53,370
No. Luo Yingzi.

606
00:26:53,370 --> 00:26:54,390
I didn't mean to bribe her.

607
00:26:54,390 --> 00:26:55,690
I just wanted to help her.

608
00:26:55,690 --> 00:26:56,710
I thought in in return for my favor,

609
00:26:56,710 --> 00:26:57,990
she would agree to testify for us.

610
00:26:57,990 --> 00:26:59,190
But now

611
00:26:59,190 --> 00:27:00,620
you have traded favors.

612
00:27:00,870 --> 00:27:03,080
Your behavior has constituted bribery.

613
00:27:03,080 --> 00:27:05,180
Do you know what legal liabilities that leaves you?

614
00:27:05,180 --> 00:27:07,310
Xia Shu, you already have a rich father.

615
00:27:07,310 --> 00:27:09,030
Why do you have to stick around in the firm?

616
00:27:09,030 --> 00:27:10,070
You should just go.

617
00:27:10,070 --> 00:27:10,640
Go!

618
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:11,910
Luo Yingzi, I was wrong.

619
00:27:11,910 --> 00:27:13,470
I didn't expect it to bring such serious consequences.

620
00:27:13,470 --> 00:27:14,910
I just wanted to win the case.

621
00:27:14,910 --> 00:27:16,270
I did it for justice.

622
00:27:16,520 --> 00:27:19,540
You're defiling this word. You know?

623
00:27:19,610 --> 00:27:20,670
You are a partner of the firm.

624
00:27:20,670 --> 00:27:22,400
You have your own office.

625
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:24,750
Why must you stay at our tiny place?

626
00:27:24,750 --> 00:27:26,630
I'm sorry. I admit I was wrong.

627
00:27:26,630 --> 00:27:27,790
I won't do it again.

628
00:27:27,790 --> 00:27:29,250
Please don't chase me off.

629
00:27:29,670 --> 00:27:30,710
Xia Shu, stop it.

630
00:27:30,710 --> 00:27:32,670
-Go back to your own office.
-Yingzi.

631
00:27:32,670 --> 00:27:33,270
Off you go.

632
00:27:33,510 --> 00:27:34,440
Qiu Hua, you...

633
00:27:41,510 --> 00:27:42,200
Xia Shu!

634
00:27:43,820 --> 00:27:44,420
Xia Shu!

635
00:27:45,270 --> 00:27:46,600
You must be off work now.

636
00:27:46,640 --> 00:27:47,150
Look!

637
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:48,930
I bought some roses on the way.

638
00:27:50,050 --> 00:27:51,700
I'm not off work yet.

639
00:27:52,580 --> 00:27:53,710
But you're about to.

640
00:27:53,950 --> 00:27:55,320
Didn't you say you wanted to go shopping?

641
00:27:55,320 --> 00:27:56,320
I have time for it.

642
00:27:56,380 --> 00:27:57,450
Let's go shopping.

643
00:27:58,130 --> 00:27:59,660
What are you doing in the firm?

644
00:27:59,660 --> 00:28:01,370
Why do you keep coming here?

645
00:28:01,390 --> 00:28:02,720
Do you take me as a child?

646
00:28:03,310 --> 00:28:04,110
You should go.

647
00:28:04,510 --> 00:28:05,140
Xia Shu!

648
00:28:05,900 --> 00:28:07,030
What's wrong?

649
00:28:07,270 --> 00:28:08,390
Who made you angry?

650
00:28:09,190 --> 00:28:10,190
You made me angry.

651
00:28:10,190 --> 00:28:11,310
I don't want to see you.

652
00:28:11,310 --> 00:28:12,110
Go away!

653
00:28:12,580 --> 00:28:13,070
Xia Shu.

654
00:28:13,100 --> 00:28:14,340
Didn't you hear me?

655
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:15,960
I told you go away! Go!

656
00:28:25,770 --> 00:28:26,500
See?

657
00:28:26,750 --> 00:28:28,260
Even when she's venting out anger, someone's willing to receive it.

658
00:28:28,260 --> 00:28:30,460
Who's gonna bear with us when we're mad?

659
00:28:32,140 --> 00:28:32,830
Yingzi.

660
00:28:33,860 --> 00:28:36,300
Should we continue with the case?

661
00:28:36,880 --> 00:28:38,630
We don't have any evidence now.

662
00:28:39,130 --> 00:28:40,900
What if Guo Yu wants to continue?

663
00:28:40,900 --> 00:28:41,920
Today is set for exchanging evidence.

664
00:28:41,920 --> 00:28:43,910
She hasn't even called yet.

665
00:28:44,570 --> 00:28:46,130
Is she backing down too?

666
00:28:47,570 --> 00:28:48,920
Call and ask her.

667
00:28:51,180 --> 00:28:52,110
I dare not to try.

668
00:28:54,390 --> 00:28:56,310
There is a change of situation.

669
00:28:56,390 --> 00:28:57,690
We have the obligation to inform the client.

670
00:28:57,690 --> 00:28:58,730
I know.

671
00:28:59,070 --> 00:28:59,870
I'll call her.

672
00:29:11,700 --> 00:29:12,460
Guo Yu.

673
00:29:12,610 --> 00:29:14,350
This morning, we exchanged evidence with the defendant's counsel.

674
00:29:14,350 --> 00:29:15,520
Sorry, Ms. Qiu.

675
00:29:15,550 --> 00:29:16,710
I'm a bit occupied now.

676
00:29:16,710 --> 00:29:18,330
I'll call you back. Alright?

677
00:29:18,350 --> 00:29:19,150
Sorry.

678
00:29:20,620 --> 00:29:21,380
I heard it.

679
00:29:22,780 --> 00:29:25,580
She doesn't want to continue with the case. Right?

680
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:33,320
What should we do now?

681
00:29:35,710 --> 00:29:36,970
What can we do?

682
00:29:37,990 --> 00:29:39,470
She wants to drop it.

683
00:29:40,780 --> 00:29:43,040
Even if we want to keep it going, we can't.

684
00:29:45,860 --> 00:29:47,500
At least,

685
00:29:51,290 --> 00:29:52,820
we don't need to worry about

686
00:29:52,950 --> 00:29:54,680
losing our dignity in the firm.

687
00:29:56,620 --> 00:29:59,070
When it's time to make a report,

688
00:29:59,260 --> 00:30:00,820
we can say the client chooses to give up.

689
00:30:00,820 --> 00:30:01,820
We have no choice.

690
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:07,810
This is exhausting.

691
00:30:08,630 --> 00:30:09,760
It's wearing me out.

692
00:30:12,420 --> 00:30:14,080
If you need to, take a holiday.

693
00:30:14,720 --> 00:30:15,320
By the way,

694
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:16,400
I'll ask Tao

695
00:30:16,840 --> 00:30:18,510
to give the patent case back to us.

696
00:30:18,510 --> 00:30:19,820
We'll work on it by ourselves.

697
00:30:19,820 --> 00:30:21,460
From now on, we'll focus on the cases

698
00:30:21,460 --> 00:30:23,630
that are lucrative and free of risks.

699
00:30:23,900 --> 00:30:25,110
Facing the east,

700
00:30:25,330 --> 00:30:27,350
we'll see spring and flowers out there.

701
00:30:27,350 --> 00:30:28,430
Just eat and sleep.

702
00:30:28,680 --> 00:30:30,410
Wake up and start making money.

703
00:30:30,420 --> 00:30:31,730
Life is wonderful.

704
00:30:36,540 --> 00:30:37,160
Cheers.

705
00:30:44,150 --> 00:30:45,270
I haven't cleared

706
00:30:45,270 --> 00:30:46,670
all my debts.

707
00:30:47,810 --> 00:30:49,170
In just one year,

708
00:30:49,470 --> 00:30:52,990
I was reduced from a worry-free housewife

709
00:30:53,220 --> 00:30:55,450
to a wandering bum

710
00:30:55,550 --> 00:30:57,190
in heavy debt.

711
00:30:57,450 --> 00:30:59,580
If I miss work for one day, I'll starve.

712
00:30:59,590 --> 00:31:01,290
My life is unstable.

713
00:31:01,320 --> 00:31:03,330
My job is unstable.

714
00:31:05,320 --> 00:31:08,180
Even I would laugh when I call myself a career woman.

715
00:31:08,440 --> 00:31:09,770
Who am I

716
00:31:09,990 --> 00:31:11,790
to try to get justice for others,

717
00:31:11,870 --> 00:31:13,710
and call for fair treatment for everyone?

718
00:31:13,710 --> 00:31:15,750
Who else would give themselves such a hard time?

719
00:31:15,750 --> 00:31:16,680
Not many people.

720
00:31:18,070 --> 00:31:20,130
Thank you for being brutally honest.

721
00:31:21,450 --> 00:31:23,070
You're not better than me.

722
00:31:24,010 --> 00:31:27,340
Someone harasses you but you keep silent about it.

723
00:31:28,190 --> 00:31:31,000
Then you go out and seek justice for others.

724
00:31:32,790 --> 00:31:33,610
Exactly.

725
00:31:34,150 --> 00:31:34,750
Come on.

726
00:31:35,010 --> 00:31:37,140
Will it kill you to say a few more words?

727
00:31:39,350 --> 00:31:40,610
I'll say one word then.

728
00:31:41,350 --> 00:31:41,860
Cheers!

729
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:43,150
Cheers!

730
00:31:43,620 --> 00:31:44,670
Qiu Hua, listen.

731
00:31:44,860 --> 00:31:45,920
Don't drink it yet.

732
00:31:46,230 --> 00:31:47,750
Let's swear an oath.

733
00:31:48,510 --> 00:31:50,890
If we ever give ourselves a hard time again,

734
00:31:50,890 --> 00:31:52,950
we'll never be able to make any money.

735
00:31:54,870 --> 00:31:55,230
Okay.

736
00:31:55,230 --> 00:31:56,440
You'd better remember what you said.

737
00:31:56,440 --> 00:31:57,080
Chug it.

738
00:31:56,540 --> 00:31:58,960
[Mom]

739
00:32:00,340 --> 00:32:01,070
What's more,

740
00:32:01,590 --> 00:32:03,600
I'll talk to Tao tomorrow

741
00:32:04,350 --> 00:32:05,610
and get that case back.

742
00:32:05,980 --> 00:32:07,660
This is only our first case.

743
00:32:08,230 --> 00:32:10,770
There will be tons of 500,000-worth cases,

744
00:32:10,790 --> 00:32:12,660
or one million-worth cases coming our way.

745
00:32:12,660 --> 00:32:14,990
Soon we'll be very rich.

746
00:32:18,560 --> 00:32:20,020
Even if it can't come true,

747
00:32:20,910 --> 00:32:22,610
it's quite pleasant to just think about it.

748
00:32:22,610 --> 00:32:24,780
Why do you have to be a buzzkill?

749
00:32:24,840 --> 00:32:26,350
Here's a punishment for you: chug it.

750
00:32:26,350 --> 00:32:26,970
I'll drink with you.

751
00:32:26,970 --> 00:32:28,090
I won't be a buzzkill anymore.

752
00:32:28,090 --> 00:32:30,360
Cheers for our extremely shallow pockets.

753
00:32:30,360 --> 00:32:32,650
You're so mean.

754
00:32:39,800 --> 00:32:42,740
[Mom]

755
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:44,640
I need to get my mom's call.

756
00:32:49,520 --> 00:32:50,320
Hey, mom.

757
00:32:53,520 --> 00:32:54,520
I'm working late.

758
00:32:54,970 --> 00:32:55,940
I've told you

759
00:32:55,970 --> 00:32:57,650
not to call me so often.

760
00:33:01,310 --> 00:33:03,440
I haven't got this month's salary yet.

761
00:33:03,780 --> 00:33:04,710
When I get it,

762
00:33:04,830 --> 00:33:06,390
I'll transfer money to you immediately.

763
00:33:06,390 --> 00:33:07,430
Stop rushing me.

764
00:33:07,440 --> 00:33:09,100
Why do you rush me every month?

765
00:33:14,270 --> 00:33:16,630
I don't want to talk about this now, okay?

766
00:33:17,990 --> 00:33:19,390
I'll call you back later.

767
00:33:31,950 --> 00:33:32,940
Are you crazy?

768
00:33:33,980 --> 00:33:35,630
Who is crazy?

769
00:33:37,950 --> 00:33:38,580
Are you okay?

770
00:33:38,580 --> 00:33:39,900
It's so embarrassing.

771
00:33:40,630 --> 00:33:43,690
I've just given Chen Shuo another reason to laugh at me.

772
00:33:43,800 --> 00:33:46,270
He doesn't know why we're dropping the case.

773
00:33:46,640 --> 00:33:47,300
It's not like that.

774
00:33:47,300 --> 00:33:49,520
I can lose to anyone, but him.

775
00:33:50,320 --> 00:33:51,420
Technically speaking, you didn't lose.

776
00:33:51,420 --> 00:33:52,950
You haven't fought him in court yet.

777
00:33:52,950 --> 00:33:54,030
One day, I will.

778
00:33:54,050 --> 00:33:54,870
I hate him so much.

779
00:33:54,870 --> 00:33:55,830
Come on. Have a drink.

780
00:33:55,830 --> 00:33:56,710
More drinks?

781
00:33:56,890 --> 00:33:58,190
I... I just threw up what I had drunk.

782
00:33:58,190 --> 00:33:58,870
Now I'm sober.

783
00:33:58,870 --> 00:33:59,980
Here comes the second round.

784
00:33:59,980 --> 00:34:00,960
Gosh.

785
00:34:48,590 --> 00:34:50,429
No matter how poor I am,

786
00:34:50,429 --> 00:34:51,659
I won't sell these two watches.

787
00:34:51,659 --> 00:34:53,460
These are my last decent things.

788
00:34:53,699 --> 00:34:55,060
I need them for negotiation meetings.

789
00:34:55,060 --> 00:34:57,190
Do you keep your car for the same reason?

790
00:34:57,190 --> 00:34:58,830
Why did you choose a red car?

791
00:34:58,950 --> 00:35:00,320
Red brings wealth.

792
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:04,150
When I'm officially divorced,

793
00:35:04,150 --> 00:35:05,510
I'll get a pink one

794
00:35:05,990 --> 00:35:06,850
to attract men.

795
00:35:07,610 --> 00:35:09,420
Your old blue car seemed too shy.

796
00:35:09,740 --> 00:35:11,000
That's why I divorced.

797
00:35:13,790 --> 00:35:16,160
Your red car is quite eye-catching.

798
00:35:16,540 --> 00:35:18,740
I'm just not sure if it'll bring you wealth.

799
00:35:18,740 --> 00:35:20,140
It's a great match for me.

800
00:35:20,290 --> 00:35:21,750
I can't keep a low profile.

801
00:35:22,690 --> 00:35:24,690
-Righteous Luo.
-Look, today, I...

802
00:35:25,310 --> 00:35:25,950
Unscrupulous Chen.

803
00:35:25,950 --> 00:35:27,010
Come on. Sit down.

804
00:35:27,680 --> 00:35:28,970
Take a seat and have a drink.

805
00:35:28,970 --> 00:35:29,780
I'm happy today.

806
00:35:29,780 --> 00:35:31,170
We'll keep drinking till we can't.

807
00:35:31,170 --> 00:35:32,830
Waiter, can you get me a glass?

808
00:35:32,990 --> 00:35:34,670
Now you're just slurring words.

809
00:35:34,670 --> 00:35:36,000
Did you drive a car here?

810
00:35:36,590 --> 00:35:37,810
Mind your own business.

811
00:35:37,810 --> 00:35:39,610
It's not like I'm minding yours.

812
00:35:39,870 --> 00:35:40,500
How much did you drink?

813
00:35:40,500 --> 00:35:42,190
Do you remember where you live?

814
00:35:42,190 --> 00:35:43,330
I'll be a nice guy today

815
00:35:43,330 --> 00:35:44,930
and give you a ride. Alright?

816
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:47,240
Don't pretend

817
00:35:47,470 --> 00:35:49,070
to be a gentleman.

818
00:35:49,560 --> 00:35:52,090
I'm telling you, people are lining up to drive me home.

819
00:35:52,090 --> 00:35:53,530
I don't need you.

820
00:35:53,560 --> 00:35:54,160
I know.

821
00:35:54,340 --> 00:35:57,200
Do you wanna be caught driving under the influence?

822
00:35:57,500 --> 00:35:59,190
Who am I supposed to fight in court then?

823
00:35:59,190 --> 00:36:01,520
I don't enjoy crushing others except you.

824
00:36:01,590 --> 00:36:02,480
You?

825
00:36:03,870 --> 00:36:04,950
You won the previous lawsuit

826
00:36:04,950 --> 00:36:06,490
because you borrowed our ideas.

827
00:36:06,490 --> 00:36:07,540
Don't be so smug about it.

828
00:36:07,540 --> 00:36:09,400
Fine. Yes. I borrowed your ideas.

829
00:36:09,440 --> 00:36:10,470
Come on. I'll take you home.

830
00:36:10,470 --> 00:36:11,430
Don't touch me.

831
00:36:11,430 --> 00:36:13,430
I'm telling you, I'm very ticklish.

832
00:36:13,990 --> 00:36:14,840
I don't need you.

833
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:15,560
See?

834
00:36:15,580 --> 00:36:16,990
The red car over there.

835
00:36:17,400 --> 00:36:18,070
It's mine.

836
00:36:18,070 --> 00:36:19,790
I know you own a red car.

837
00:36:19,790 --> 00:36:21,430
-A red car. Right?
-You betcha.

838
00:36:21,430 --> 00:36:22,390
I got it. I got it.

839
00:36:22,510 --> 00:36:23,070
Ms. Qiu,

840
00:36:23,290 --> 00:36:24,510
come on. I'll drive you both home.

841
00:36:24,510 --> 00:36:25,910
